The paper deals with fault-tolerant distributed systems, specifically state machine replication, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses consensus algorithms, which are commonly used in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The LBV abstraction proposed in the paper involves composing multiple instances of consensus algorithms, which is a topic in Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The paper also deals with network asynchrony and attacks, which are topics in Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), respectively.
